div.head:
Seven Books of Mr. Jeremiah Burroughs lately published;
As also the Texts of Scripture upon
which they are grounded.

div.p:
                  THis is so wel known that it needs no Description;
I shal therfore only write the
Vertues therof, which are many.

div.head:
♀ ♈ The Bramble;
OR
Black-Berry-Bush.

div.p:
THis Tree is so well known, growing generally
in all Countries of this Land;
that it is needless to describe it.

There is another sort hereof differing not
from the former in the manner of growing,
but only that his Stalk and Branches being
somwhat greater do a little more bow down to
the ground: The Leavs are somwhat larger;
the Heads somwhat lesser, the Seed alike;
and the Root and Leavs abide all the Winter,
and perish not as the former.

OF all the kinds of Mints, the SpearMint
or Heart-Mint, being most useful;
I shal only describe it: as followeth.

THis being indeed the Key of the Work, I shall be somthing the more dilligent in it: I shall deliver my self thus;
1. To the Vulgar.
2. To Such as study Astrology, or such as study Physick Astrologically.
